cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on training deep neural networks with high computational and energy requirements. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel training strategy that utilizes Net2Net transformation, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the reduction in computational complexity achieved through this strategy, which is related to optimization techniques in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions pruning during Net2Net expansion, which is a technique used to reduce the size of neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the improved adversarial input detection achieved through mutual inference from all the networks created with cumulative Net2Net expansion, which is related to computer security and falls under the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
